  },
  "//overrides": {
    "@blaze-cardano/core": "Collapse duplicate copies (0.7.x vs 0.8.0). cosponsor-sdk@0.0.1 still declares ^0.7.0, so without this pin Bun keeps a 0.7.x subtree. Duplicate Core.Transaction prototypes surface as `*.toCore is not a function` at runtime.",
    "@blaze-cardano/uplc": "Same problem one level deeper: cosponsor-sdk@0.0.1 pins ^0.3.2 (resolves to 0.3.9, which exact-pins @blaze-cardano/core 0.7.0). The blaze-cardano/core override alone does NOT cascade into a nested-version subtree, so we also force uplc itself to 0.4.3 (the version built against core 0.8.0). Symptom this fixes: `address.toCore is not a function` when calling browserDeposit's txBuilder.complete().",
    "@cardano-sdk/core": "Collapse duplicate copies (0.45.0 vs 0.46.12). wallet-lite peer-deps 0.45.0 exactly while dapp-connector wants ~0.46.12 — semver-incompatible. Without this override, two TransactionUnspentOutput prototypes coexist and CIP-30 plumbing breaks."
  },
  "overrides": {
    "@blaze-cardano/core": "0.8.0",
    "@blaze-cardano/uplc": "0.4.3",
    "@cardano-sdk/core": "0.46.12"
  }
}
